ProblemSolution
The flash does not fire.The flash is disabled: Adjust settings (□□ 180). The electronicshutter is enabled: Choose a SHUTTER TYPE that does not use the electronic shutter ( == 170). The battery is exhausted: Charge the battery or insert a ful- ly-charged spare battery (� 42). The camera is in bracketing or continuous mode: Select single frame mode (□ 6).
The flash does not fully light the subject.The subject is not in range of the flash: Position the subject in range of the flash. ● The flash window is obstructed: Hold the camera correctly. Shutter speed is faster than the sync speed: Choose a slower shutter speed ( 74, 80, 398).
